					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">According to <a href="http://nesdev.com/Ntd_8bit.jpg" class="postlink">this shematic</a>, the microphone input goes to a low pass filter made with a 10k resistor and 0.1uF capacity, whose constant of time equals 1ms. So the bit read cannot change faster than 1ms no matter what causes it to change.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
