						<div class="postbody">Except it is fed to the input of a logic gate, which is a non-linear element, thus the spectrum of input doesn't tell us that of output. It could go just above the threshold, then just below it, and cause two changes within any amount of time. This is almost comical now; I don't see why having this work with the Famicom microphone is so important. What we really need is someone to run some test code on the Famicom with a mic and get actual behavior, though that still wouldn't tell us rare behavior. Maybe I should just ignore the subject further? <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

