						<div class="postbody">Well I guess you're right. The gate isn't a shmitt trigger so what you describe is likely to be happening.
<br />I find it's stupid to make code that is working on one type of machine but not another for stupid details like that. If you made code that runs on NTSC, then I'd assume it would run on all licenced NTSC NESes, NES2 and Famicoms in the world, not rely on unstable things. PAL only code can use tricks that don't work on the FC I guess, but I wouldn't made PAL only code myself.</div>

					
