						<div class="postbody">I've got a Famicom and can run tests, but I don't know what specifically we're testing for. If you guys didn't know, there's a slide pot on the mic to control volume so that will surely affect the results. Because the mic is pretty sensitive, most Famicom players will have the mic always turned off so ambient noise doesn't overwhelm the game's sound, on my main system I have entirely disconnected player 2 for this reason. So I don't think dealing with the mic bit is a big deal, I'd just assume it's off.</div>

