						<div class="postbody">So you ran the test ROM, then held B on the second controller and it just kept printing 0 twice a second? If not, the source code is pretty simple.
<br />
<br />I noticed I wasn't initializing $4000 and was relying on the default initialization on the NES to 0. I added explicit initialization of $4000-$4002 to 0. I tested and it wouldn't have printed anything if the default initialization was wrong, so this probably wasn't the cause of your issue. Just fixing this on the slim chance it was the cause: <a href="http://h1.ripway.com/blargg/temp/fast_joy_famicom_test2.zip" class="postlink">fast_joy_famicom_test2.zip</a></div>

